    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Considering the parallelism of our test-suite, I'd expect resource allocation issues is not limited to just PTYs. If we're running into this, we could instead consider upping limits, reducing parallelism, or going over which are the main problematic tests and remove parallelism from those (e.g. no `t.Parallel()`).\n\nThe main problems I see with this approach is adding test-code to a production package (have we considered build-flags?) and all the edge-cases in which it breaks (accurate detection of active parallelism, assumption that the rest of the system isn't under load, breaking expectations of typical context-timeouts in tests). We're also assuming each package is doing PTY testing which is unlikely to be the case. Without verification, I'd expect this number to be around 3-5 packages in total.",
    "commit_id": "47687fd4be80bc0fd8795efd2718630ec6adb29a",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/coder/coder/pull/21981#pullrequestreview-3783535694",
